Scaling Numerical Data:
This ensures the numeric variables are on the same scale. Z-score standardization was applied to the numeric values to place them on a common scale. The data is around the mean (0) and scales based on the standard deviation. The values represent how many standard deviations each observation is from the mean. All numeric data was scaled.

scaled_data <- skew_data

num_col <- names(scaled_data)[sapply(scaled_data, is.numeric)]

scaled_data[num_col] <- scale(scaled_data[num_col])

